Package smeen.component.code

Class CodeBlockInputSlot<T>

java.lang.Object
javafx.scene.Node
javafx.scene.Parent
javafx.scene.layout.Region
javafx.scene.layout.Pane
javafx.scene.layout.StackPane
smeen.component.code.CodeBlockInputSlot<T>
Type Parameters:
T - the type of result this CodeBlockInputSlot will evaluate to.
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget, Savable
public class CodeBlockInputSlot<T> extends javafx.scene.layout.StackPane implements Savable
Represent slots found in CodeBlocks that accept CodeBlockInput to evaluate to values to be given to CodeBlock. If there's no CodeBlockInput in the slot, there will be a text field that accept user's direct string input.

      public T getValue(SmeenContext context)
      Evaluate the current code block input slot. If there's CodeBlockInput present, this will evaluate to the result of that CodeBlockInput, otherwise this will evaluate to the text (converted into correct type) of the text field in this slot.
      Parameters:
      context - the context to be used.
      Returns:
      the result of evaluation.
